text:
This could well be the flagship store of Kim San Leng - arguably one of Singapore's oldest, largest chain and successful "kopitiam."

It has evolved from a gamble start-up in Yishun Town to a multifaceted chain.

I will always make it a point to ear at this outlet whenever I AK in the area. It offers a good selection of not-so-humble foodstalls.

My favorite ones are: economic rice or porridge, tai seng fish soup, the fish ball noodles and the prawn noodles.

The coffee is nice but the drink service staff is horrible. Came in the morning and she never ask me what i want even tho i am next in queue to order. As i see she was doing some other drinks so i didnt say what i want. And the next thing she say,‚Äù you must tell me what you want‚Äù in mandarin. Bro‚Ä¶. Before that she was alrdy complaining about a customer at the front for not ordering and kept talking. We will order if you are ready. If you are not ready, how do we dare to order?
The only cai fan stall , btg a packet of plain white for work. But found some sus thing like rat droppings. ü§ÆGot hair somemore!
Ridiculous expensive economy veg rice stall. Got charged $5.90 for this. Meat is hard as rock and rice is sticky. Avoid at all cost.

In this day and age when it is hard to find a good value and tasty economical rice stall, the one here is not bad. The young men behind the counter are fairly friendly. A bit cramped for space but acceptable.
